<h1>@HI{{tsumori}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> @Vru{{}}@HI{{ <strong>tsumori</strong>desu}}
<li> @Vnai{{}}@HI{{ <strong>tsumori</strong>desu}}
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
The @Vru{{}} form indicates the speaker's intention of doing something.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{country}}he @KJ{{homecoming}}ttemo,@KJ{{tender^road-way}}wo @KJ{{continue}}keru <strong>tsumori</strong>desu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Even when I go back to my country, I'll continue my judo.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
The @HI{{nai}} form indicates the speaker's intention of not doing something.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{ashita karaha tabakowo @KJ{{suck}}wanai <strong>tsumori</strong>desu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I'm determined not to smoke from tomorrow.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<h2> Notes </h2>

<p>
Compared with @Vyou{{}} @HI{{to @KJ{{think}}tteimasu}}, @Vru{{}}@HI{{<strong>tsumori</strong>desu.}} sounds more determined.
</p>

